    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted at Medium assurance level because: (1) ASTM F1717 is a standardized single-condition protocol accepted by FDA; (2) all three QoIs satisfy quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%) across two independent laboratories and three independent modeling teams; (3) model risk level 3 is adequately supported by the overall evidence body at Medium assurance. Package conforms to ProfileMinimal; digital signature is pending completion of the institutional signature workflow and has not been applied to this package.",
